text: Groß-Gerau is the capital of Groß-Gerau in Hesse, Germany. It is in the southern Frankfurt Rhein-Main Region and its surrounding area. == Twin towns == Groß-Gerau is twinned with: * Brignoles, France (1959) * Bruneck, Italy (1959) * Tielt, Belgium (1959) * Szamotuły, Poland (2000) == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:Groß-Gerau (district)
